[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering dynamic class loading options**\n\nI need to add a test file for handling lower version branches, but it's tricky due to classloader limitations with static fields. I’m thinking about using a dynamic-access report to check if isolated classloaders can load Freemarker classes. Tests should avoid reflection unless necessary. Maybe the URLClassLoader is an option, but it has its own challenges. Could creating child classloaders with test classes and manipulating the static version of PySystemState work? It’s all quite complex!\n\n**Exploring test method options**\n\nI'm considering whether to use separate test methods with a launched Java process, but that might not be native. I want to ensure there's dynamic access to the target in the test process. It seems the agent won’t follow child JVMs, so using actual public fields instead of reflection looks necessary. The `PySystemState.version` is a public static String, so I'm thinking of importing it and assigning values. I also wonder if JUnit can fork per test, allowing for fresh JVM instances for each one.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02847bcd204acf4c0169f4b8ba5c04819c80a5e5bea5e71b5f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9LjBsC-oZp4dm0IMaxW9lJUy96ceXtSIA3mHF7FmZ6glmSp4jWBXBfMywt4ZERRWB6-AP4r_asZaJ_UlYHkDZ4h4bQsvhOZmbJprF-eCgbwLPcAgvOL7ABfOEfxJqqYMZE9NucHsqHk6WczR2gTdOpWRSg85va9U7zTHniIa1R89URnqBZssoy_RMGxcepryfsxZa29W3ENcDrMATQcrXMURCtGo-7orlQTOkGYfTzyJNdK0Hdr8j434x14bQhiWM7yMMZ6Md3dHuj1Xpyb-4JpOTwdeQZ3IF266pmAK5L4CkvHSLBI1u7258irYgK6tH9z5w4KeGXJQuPNDjzn-zNMz_TU8vPW4EYE_tOOHW2FRQZBO0eoSh8jAeE2cbINYykFp8VCaST09b1ExezkkLPsOG-Lxf7HYwyKZFzHPc_vO9qZGwKDx_b7QYuMKySizPFqLAOw3Ai0sqWg3kmV4F1i-uBdJM1GXEJvc_FBjjJLcPG0-j1acKmdDWUKq5KRmITghahROzrWGptvJcTRnz6kffNX1hjkoE1tWg3-7e100sZdHw9L4RMn-JKZb2cg-Z6MgpUOZaGSGe4Gt_MkaIZa2uUZ0eNSn48M9bpaPW-WZUBh05gq05nRacL2pQDb3GjoCybgUp7ra6j2nVAqsxp